SOCCER 10 POOL OF THE DAYThursday 10 March S10 V2 Leeds will be looking to provide their new manager with a first home success as they host Aston Villa, with a victory also important in the relegation battle. More details at www.soccer6.co.za. M1 PAOK Salonika vs KAA Gent: PAOK registered 11 points in finishing second to FC Copenhagen in their Europa Conference League group, before overcoming another Danish side, Midtjylland, 5-3 on penalties in the knockout round play-off. Gent cruised directly into the round of 16 after topping their group with 13 points.M2 Partizan Belgrade vs Feyenoord Rotterdam: Two clubs who began their Europa Conference League journey in the second qualifying round meet with a place in the quarter-finals at stake as European perennials Partizan and Feyenoord go head to head in UEFA competition for the first time.M3 Sevilla vs West Ham United: Sevilla’s bid to win the Europa League for the fifth time – with this season’s final taking place at their own stadium – continues with a testing round of 16 tie against Premier League high fliers West Ham.M4 Slavia Prague vs LASK Linz: Slavia’s 13th match in an eventful 2021/22 continental campaign brings them a first meeting with LASK as they host the first leg of their Europa Conference League round of 16 tie against a team with a flawless record on the road in Europe this season.M5 Vitesse Arnhem vs Roma: Vitesse were runners-up to Rennes in Europa Conference League Group G on 10 points before coming from behind to eliminate Rapid Wien in last week’s play-offs. Despite the shock of a 6-1 defeat away to Bodø/Glimt, Roma pipped the Norwegian champions to top spot in Group C, scoring 18 goals – the most of any team in the group stage.M6 Stjarnan vs Breidablik: Stjarnan beat Breidablik 3-1 to win the pre-season Football Net Cup in Iceland and now they meet again in the League Cup.M7 Southampton vs Newcastle United: After three successive wins, the Saints lost 4-0 to Aston Villa on Saturday. Newcastle have now gone seven games without defeat as they climb clear of relegation danger.M8 Leeds United vs Aston Villa: Leeds are on a five match losing streak. Villa have won their last two games, scoring six goals without conceding,M9 Barcelona vs Galatasaray: Barcelona’s quest for the one major international trophy missing from their collection continues with a Europa League round of 16 tie against former UEFA Cup winners Galatasaray.M10 Olympique de Marseille vs FC Basel: Marseille are unbeaten at home to Swiss visitors and have won two of their three knockout ties against opposition from the country. Basel’s record against French clubs is W4 D4 L5, but they have never won in France. Suggested permutation: R32.00 1 x 2,3 x 1,2 x 1 x 2,3 x 1 x 1 x 2,3 x 1 x 1